{"id":833,"date":"2022-01-20T16:29:43","date_gmt":"2022-01-20T16:29:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=833"},"modified":"2022-01-20T16:29:48","modified_gmt":"2022-01-20T16:29:48","slug":"boot-reboot-and-shut-down-a-system-normally","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=833","title":{"rendered":"Boot, reboot, and shut down a system normally"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>You should first understand how exactly the boot process works. I&#8217;m going to use this image I&#8217;ve found on <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/nu11secur1ty\/All-Stages-of-Linux-Booting-Process-\">github<\/a>. The picture is pretty much self-explanatory, so I don&#8217;t think it needs further commenting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"661\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?resize=640%2C661&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-834\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?w=666&amp;ssl=1 666w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?resize=290%2C300&amp;ssl=1 290w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?resize=24%2C24&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?resize=36%2C36&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-133.png?resize=46%2C48&amp;ssl=1 46w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Boot, reboot and shutdown can be done in multiple ways<\/strong>, as all the time in Linux. The GUI way in which you click power off button, reboot button it simple and everyone who uses PC at least once a year know how to do it.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You simple click on the power on\/off icon in the upper right corner and choose the option you want to use.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"102\" height=\"29\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-134.png?resize=102%2C29&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-835\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-134.png?w=102&amp;ssl=1 102w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-134.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-134.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-134.png?resize=48%2C14&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 102px) 100vw, 102px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"535\" height=\"182\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?resize=535%2C182&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-836\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?w=535&amp;ssl=1 535w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?resize=300%2C102&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-135.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 535px) 100vw, 535px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Using terminal<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The terminal way is the one necessary to know for Linux administrator. <strong>The main used command is shutdown<\/strong>. We can list all use cases of this command with <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">man shutdown<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"463\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?resize=640%2C463&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-837\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?w=736&amp;ssl=1 736w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?resize=300%2C217&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?resize=24%2C17&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?resize=36%2C26&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-136.png?resize=48%2C35&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Shutdown the system<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The main used command is<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown -H now<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>The -H flag, as you can read above, is an option for halting the system. This is important because from my experience sometimes the system can hang, this is especially bad if the system is physical and you can no longer connect to the system via SSH.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Most of the time you should be using the power off option aka -h.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><code>halt<\/code>\u00a0terminates all processes and shuts down the cpu.<\/p><p><code>poweroff<\/code>\u00a0is exactly like\u00a0<code>halt<\/code>, but it also turns off the unit itself (lights and everything on a PC). It sends an ACPI command to the board, then to the PSU, to cut the power.<\/p><p><code>shutdown<\/code>\u00a0is like\u00a0<code>poweroff<\/code>, but it also runs shutdown scripts which should stop things gracefully. Examples include giving programs a chance to close files, delete their lock files and unmount drives properly.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The now option executes the command immediately. Without this flag, the shutdown would occur after 1 minute of waiting time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, it is important to note you need sudo privileges or root user to execute the command.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can change the time parameter to specific time. For example<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flex wp-container-7 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown -h 03:00 \nYou can also execute this command with comment which will be display for all user on the system<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown +2 The system is going down for required maintenance. Please save any important work you are doing now! <\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>There is also an option -k which will only send the message and not shutdown nor reboot system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown -k<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Reboot the system<\/strong> <\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For the reboot we can again use the shutdown command with -r flag for reboot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown -r now<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>Or we can use reboot command which is the same thing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">reboot now <\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We can again use the same time or command principle as with the shutdown -h command.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cancel the shutdown\/reboot<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>And the last but not least, I&#8217;ll show you the option for canceling scheduled shutdown or reboot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The syntax for command is again very simple, we use -c flag for cancel<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">shutdown -c <\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You should first understand how exactly the boot process works. I&#8217;m going to use this [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":840,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[313,314,220,315,316],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-operate-running-systems.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/833"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=833"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/833\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":842,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/833\/revisions\/842"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/840"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=833"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=833"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=833"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}